item.description:
For any morphism $f:T	o S$ in the underlying triangulated category $D$, complete the (distinguished triangle) $T	o S	o R\xrightarrow{+1}$. If there exists a decomposition of $f$, i.e. $\exists X\in\mathrm{ob}(D)$ and $T\xrightarrow{
u}X\xrightarrow{\gamma}S$ such that $f=\gamma\circ
u$, then complete the (distinguished) triangles induced by $
u$ and $\gamma$, i.e. $$T \xrightarrow{
u} X \xrightarrow{\gamma&rsquo;} S&rsquo;\xrightarrow{+1}$$ and $$T&rsquo; \xrightarrow{
u&rsquo;} X \xrightarrow{\gamma} S\xrightarrow{+1}$$. Do the same operation again, complete the (distinguished) triangle induced by $f&rsquo;=\gamma&rsquo;\circ
u&rsquo;$, i.e. $$T&rsquo; \xrightarrow{\gamma&rsquo;\circ
u&rsquo;}S&rsquo; \xrightarrow{ y} R&rsquo;\xrightarrow{+1}$$.
